******
[2] Brazil
Date: Sat 14 Feb 2008
Source: Ministry of Health/Secretariat Of Health Monitoring Daily
Bulletin [edited]
<http://portal.saude.gov.br/portal/arquivos/pdf/boletimfA_140208.pdf>


As of 14 Feb 2008, the epidemiological situation is that there has
been notification of 57 suspected cases of yellow fever (YF). Of
these, 30 cases were confirmed, of which 15 died (case fatality rate
of 50 percent). Another 23 cases were negative for YF, and 4 remain
under investigation.

The likely sites of infection of the confirmed cases occurred in
forested areas of Goias, 64 percent [of the cases] (19/30), Mato
Grosso do Sul, 20 percent (6/30), Federal District 13 percent (4/30)
and Mato Grosso 3 percent (1/30).

The distribution of cases and deaths from sylvan yellow fever by date
of onset of symptoms shows the 1st confirmed case on 16 Dec 2007 and
the latest suspected case on 25 Jan 2008.

[YF cases in humans and monkeys continue to occur. See the original
bulletin, which has maps, graphics and tables at the URL cited above.
- Mod.LJS]

